value.value: A finding indicating the presence of large ganglion cells, neural cellular infiltrates and a stroma with Schwannian differentiation in a neoplastic tissue specimen.

A sex cord-stromal tumor occurring in the ovary and testis. In females it occurs predominantly in the first three decades of life and presents unilaterally as stage I disease in the vast majority of cases. It is characterized by the presence of granulosa cells forming macrofollicular structures. The majority of cases have a good prognosis. In males it represents the most frequent congenital testicular neoplasm, and the vast majority of cases occur in the perinatal period. It presents as a scrotal or abdominal mass, and it more often affects the left testis. Approximately 20% of the patients have ambiguous external genitalia. It is characterized by the presence of cystic spaces lined by granulosa cells and cells resembling theca cells. Metastases have not been reported.

label.value: Scattered Collections of Differentiating Neuroblasts Present

value.value: A morphologic finding indicating the presence of an abnormal or aberrant cellular component in an organ sample.
A morphological finding where an influx of cells is detected in locations or numbers that those cells are not normally found.
The epithelium of the choroid plexus; which consists of cuboidal cells.

label.value: Ovarian Sex Cord Tumor with Annular Tubules

value.value: An ovarian sex cord-stromal tumor characterized by the presence of Sertoli cells forming annular tubules. It may be associated with Peutz-Jeghers syndrome. Cases associated with Peutz-Jeghers syndrome have followed a benign clinical course. Cases which are not associated with Peutz-Jeghers syndrome have been reported having a clinically malignant course.
A neoplasm that arises from the choroid plexus in the brain and occurs during childhood.
Vertical strabismus in which there is permanent downward deviation of the visual axis of one eye.

label.value: Aggregates of Poorly Differentiated Neuroepithelial Cells Present

value.value: Malformation of the cerebral cortex due to improper migration of neurons in utero.

label.value: Well Differentiated Ovarian Sertoli-Leydig Cell Tumor

value.value: A Sertoli-Leydig tumor of the ovary characterized by the presence of Sertoli cells in tubules without evidence of significant nuclear atypia or mitotic activity. Primitive gonadal stromal cells are not present. It usually follows a benign clinical course.
A purine nucleoside comprised of a guanine bound to the 1' position of deoxyribose. Phosphorylated forms of deoxyguanosine are substrates for DNA synthesis.

label.value: Poorly Differentiated Ovarian Sertoli-Leydig Cell Tumor

value.value: A Sertoli-Leydig tumor of the ovary characterized by the presence of a sarcomatoid stroma which contains primitive gonadal stromal cells. It may behave in a malignant fashion and metastasize to other anatomic sites.

label.value: Ovarian Sertoli Cell Tumor with Lipid Storage

value.value: A Sertoli cell tumor that arises from the ovary and is characterized by the presence of cells that are distended by the presence of intracytoplasmic lipid.
